The paper focuses on generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image generation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves multiple generator networks, which can be considered as an ensemble learning method, and the use of gating networks, which is a common technique in neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of categorical reparameterization trick, which is a technique in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the evaluation of the proposed approach on CelebA dataset, which is a popular dataset for face recognition and image generation, and CIFAR-10, which is a popular dataset for image classification, both of which fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
